dataIdInfo.idPurp: Watershed layer, with area in square meters, for Santa Rosa Island watersheds of > 5ha. The watersheds are generated from 2010 lidar DEMs (1m cell size, 15cm vertical accuracy).
dataIdInfo.idAbs: Watersheds were generated from 2010 lidar DEMs (1m cell size, 15cm vertical accuracy). ArcToolbox (10.0) tools were used. DEMs were clipped at the 2 m contour line (generated from same lidar data) to prevent intersection with the ocean. Basic progression was to to use Flow Direction tool, then Sink tool, then Fill tool, then Basin tool, then Raster To Polygon tool to produce a watershed shapefile. This shapefile then had all basins < 50,000 sq m removed.
